comments.body:
@techievivek I'm sorry it took me so long but I had to read all the mentioned comments and threads to get an understanding about the issue we are trying to solve here.

So, the issue here is that we have double `withOnyx` used because we are relying in the second one on the value added to props in the first one - is it correct? Then I think the change to the `react-native-onyx` introduced by this PR: https://github.com/Expensify/react-native-onyx/pull/385 could potentially allow us moving the key from the second `withOnyx` to the first one and this way getting rid of the second one, as @pradeepmdk suggested in [their proposal](https://github.com/Expensify/App/issues/29165#issuecomment-1754840362).

But first, I wonder how could I test it - if I understand correctly there should be some new option in `/settings/profile` related to notifications, am I right? I can't see such option so what do I need to do to enable it?
